<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../helpproject.xsl" ?>
<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Customize</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading2_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Customize</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The menu items under Customize are listed in table 12. The commands under this menu are used to change how ModelMuse behaves.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Table Caption"><text styleclass="Table Caption" translate="true">Table 12. Customize Menu</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:center;"><table rowcount="9" colcount="2" style="width:auto; cell-padding:4px; cell-spacing:0px; page-break-inside:auto; border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; background-color:none; head-row-background-color:none; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Menu Item</text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Explanation</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Font... </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">Change the font used throughout ModelMuse.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Color... </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">Change the background color of the windows used throughout ModelMuse.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Hint Display Time... </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">Change how long “hints” are displayed. See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Hint_Display_Time_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Table Cell" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Hint Display Time</link><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Ruler Format... </text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">Change the numeric format of the Rulers. See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Ruler_Format_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Table Cell" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ruler Format</link><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Batch File Additions...</text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">Insert extra lines into the batch used to run the model. See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Batch_File_Additions_Dialog" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Batch File Additions</link><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Show Tips</text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">If Show Tips is checked, ModelMuse will check the ModelMuse web site once a day for any web pages with tips on how to use ModelMuse. If there are any such web pages that it has not already displayed, ModelMuse will display one of them. Many of these web pages contain videos.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Show or Hide Rulers</text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">This menu item can be used to hide or display the rulers on the top, front, and side views of the model.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:137px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Header" style="text-align:left;"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Archive model by default</text></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:top; width:489px;">
          <para styleclass="Table Cell"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">If Archive model by default is checked, ModelMuse will, by default, create an archive file of the model each time you save the model. See also: </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Files_to_Archive_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Files to Archive</link><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true"> dialog box</text><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
